Described by chair of judges Kate Williams as a book that “shines a light on today’s America”, Jones’s fourth novel An American Marriage won the £30,000 award on Wednesday night.
With fans including Oprah Winfrey and Barack Obama, the novel follows ambitious newlyweds Celestial and Roy.
The novel won from a six-book shortlist that included last year’s Booker winner, Anna Burns’s Milkman, and former Booker winner Pat Barker’s new novel, The Silence of the Girls.
“And I was like, ‘You know, I don’t know him, but I know she’s probably right.
The Women’s prize is the UK’s only book award for fiction by women.